TITLE: Run Command Example (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: This TypeScript code snippet demonstrates how to make a POST request to the '/api/git' endpoint to run a command in a repository.  It configures the 'Content-Type' and provides the action, repository path, command, arguments, and environment variables. Upon a successful response, it logs the command output; otherwise, it logs an error message.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mario-andreschak/flujo/blob/main/src/app/api/git/README.md#_snippet_15

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const response = await fetch('/api/git', {
  method: 'POST',
  headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
  body: JSON.stringify({
    action: 'run',
    savePath: '/path/to/repo',
    runCommand: 'npm start',
    args: ['--port', '3000'],
    env: { 'NODE_ENV': 'development' }
  })
});

const data = await response.json();
if (data.success) {
  console.log(`Command output: ${data.commandOutput}`);
} else {
  console.error(`Error: ${data.error}`);
}
```

