TITLE: Using Model Frontend Service Methods in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to import and use the methods provided by the Model frontend service to interact with the backend API. It shows examples for loading models, getting a specific model, adding a new model, updating an existing model, and deleting a model. It assumes that `modelService` is properly initialized and configured.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mario-andreschak/flujo/blob/main/src/frontend/services/model/README.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
// Import the frontend service
